# Notification Service — Manual Test Requests
#
# Prerequisites:
#   1. Run backend: cd backend && uvicorn main:app --reload --port 8000
#   2. Open the app in Expo Go on your device — HomeScreen will print to console:
#        [DEBUG] Expo push token: ExponentPushToken[...]
#        [DEBUG] Firebase ID token: eyJ...
#   3. Paste those values into the variables below.
#
# USER_ID is pre-filled. Replace PUSH_TOKEN and FIREBASE_TOKEN after running the app.

# Variables (fill these in after running the app on device)
# PUSH_TOKEN     = ExponentPushToken[xxxx]   (from Expo Go console)
# FIREBASE_TOKEN = eyJ...                    (from Expo Go console, expires in 1h)
# DEVICE_ID      = any string, e.g. "my-iphone"

@base = https://functions-eight-topaz.vercel.app


### ── 1. Register your ntfy topic as push token ─────────────────────────────
# Replace screentimeapp-romanos-test with whatever topic you subscribed to in the ntfy app.
# The "ntfy:" prefix tells the backend to use ntfy instead of Expo.
POST {{base}}/api/users/me/push-token
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <FIREBASE_TOKEN>

{
  "deviceId": "my-iphone",
  "expoPushToken": "ntfy:screentimeapp-romanos-test",
  "platform": "ios"
}


### ── 2. Set short thresholds for testing (30s personal, 60s friends) ──────
# Real defaults are 420s (7 min) and 900s (15 min).
PUT {{base}}/api/users/me/notification-settings
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <FIREBASE_TOKEN>

{
  "enabled": true,
  "userAlertThresholdSeconds": 30,
  "friendAlertThresholdSeconds": 60,
  "trackedApps": ["Instagram", "TikTok", "TestApp"],
  "allowFriendsToSeeLiveSessions": true,
  "sendCloseSessionSummaryToFriends": true
}


### ── 3. Simulate app OPEN ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# No auth required — uses shortcut endpoint.
# Check Firestore activeSessions collection to confirm doc appears.
POST {{base}}/api/usage/record?userId=zJHMK6iYW7M3THkCFZ2bsBv5sbG2&appName=Instagram&eventType=open&deviceId=my-iphone


### ── 4. Manually trigger the cron ─────────────────────────────────────────
# Wait 30+ seconds after step 3, then fire this.
# You should receive a push notification on your device.
POST {{base}}/api/cron/check-active-sessions


### ── 5. Simulate app CLOSE ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
POST {{base}}/api/usage/record?userId=zJHMK6iYW7M3THkCFZ2bsBv5sbG2&appName=Instagram&eventType=close&deviceId=my-iphone


### ── 6. Check live friends (should be empty after close) ───────────────────
GET {{base}}/api/users/me/live-friends
Authorization: Bearer <FIREBASE_TOKEN>


### ── 7. Shame endpoint ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Replace FRIEND_USER_ID with the UID of a user in the same group as you.
POST {{base}}/api/users/<FRIEND_USER_ID>/shame
Authorization: Bearer <FIREBASE_TOKEN>


### ── 8. Verify notification audit log in Firestore ────────────────────────
# There's no GET endpoint for this yet — check directly in Firestore console:
#   users/zJHMK6iYW7M3THkCFZ2bsBv5sbG2/notifications/
# You should see docs with type, deliveryStatus, triggeredBy, etc.
